<recipe>
    <name>Artichokes (Steamed)</name>
    <indexCharacter>A</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>4</servings>
    <instructions>Chop the stems off the artichokes until they stand flat. Put the artichokes in a Dutch Oven with enough water to allow them to float. Pour in lemon juice and garlic oil and bring the water to a boil. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer until a leaf pulls out easily, about 45 minutes.</instructions>
